President Tran Dai Quang of Vietnam has passed away, and the American people and President Donald Trump express their condolences to his family and the people of Vietnam. President Quang was a close friend of the United States and played a significant role in deepening the partnership between the two countries. He hosted President Trump during his state visit to Hanoi in 2017 and made important contributions to peace, security, and prosperity in the Indo-Pacific region. President Quang was also known for his advocacy for Vietnam as an independent nation on the global stage.